<GmapID>0x80dc749f6002c2b3:0xe3458b1592fae094< /GmapID><pics>None<//pics><UserId.>113557144647046535168</UserId.>< text>
I rarely post reviews for products online as I'm seldom impressed with a product enough to do so.  However, in this instance I feel compelled to shout this one from the rooftops!  I am the full time caregiver for my 64 spouse who I've been married to for 46 years.  She has Type II diabetes among other serious maladies, but her blood sugar drops dangerously low without warning, often in her sleep.  With the new Libre II device monitoring her levels in real time and sounding the alarm, we are able to promptly react before she goes into hypoglycemic shock.  Just as amazing is the predictive nature of the device that forecasts rising or falling trends of her lab values thus allowing us to adjust diet and other factors resulting using less insulin.  It is a game changer for us!  Finally, we are so grateful to Advanced Diabetes Supply for guiding us through the process of obtaining the device, coordinating medical records, insurance company requirements and keeping us posted every step of the way!  We dealt with a person by the name of Izzy who was professional, compassionate and kind. Thank you from the bottom of our hearts.  Please feel free to use any or all of this review.  Terry & Carrie Herman, Preston, CT</text>

<Rating>1<//Rating>< Review>
Absolutely terrible service. Not only is the phone wait time incredibly long, their suggested use of their voicemail takes no less than 24 hours and usually longer to get back to you.
I have been having an issue with my transmitter that (for some reason) was not sent with my sensor supplies. After 7 phone calls (and counting), I have still not received it. At each phone call, one issue is apparently addressed, but other issues are not. Then, I as the customer, have to continuously follow up to find out why I still haven't received my transmitter. Then another issue comes up that has to be addressed. Today my transmitter finally died so I'm back to finger sticks. I have been "guaranteed" that it was going to arrive several days ago, but still no transmitter. As a physician, my staff and I deal with various medical and medical supply companies, Advanced Diabetes Supply has been the worst experience I've had in 30+ years of practicing medicine. I spoke with my endocrinologist and she has stated that several of her other patients are having similar issues.< /Review>

< Text>
I started using ADS for my Libre sensors about 4 years ago. The first sensors were 10 day sensors at first, and now they are 14 day sensors, and better now the sensor Reader will alert one to either low or high glucose day or nite!
The service provided by Advanced Diabetes Supply has been great all of these 4 years! They have been there for me whenever I have need them. I would refer them to anyone along with the Libre sensors!</Text>

I can't even begin to express my frustration at the incompetence of ADS. Case in point: In January 2021, I called them to update our new insurance. Diabetes supplies were not due to be refilled until March, so this gave them plenty of time.

On March 2, 2021, they sent their form text asking for authorization to ship and charge the card on file. I authorized it.

On March 12, 2021, I received an email from ADS, asking for the exact same authorization. I gave it, and asked why they were emailing when they texted for the same authorization ten days earlier.

On March 23, 2021, I called ADS to find out what was going on, because supplies were about to run out. I had to wait on hold for over TWO HOURS before I finally got to speak to someone, and they couldn't figure out what was wrong with the order.

On March 24, 2021, they called me on the phone to say that they had run the insurance verification TO THE WRONG INSURANCE. Yes, they had the correct insurance on file from when I updated it back in January, but they didn't use that one; they used the previous insurance. So now they had to run a NEW insurance verification. They assured me they'd put a rush order on it, so it should be back within a couple of days. I gave my authorization at that time for them to immediately ship it, once the verification was back.

On April 15, 2021, they called me to say that the insurance verification JUST came back (???) but wouldn't authorize a 90-day supply, which we've had for over a year. They didn't offer to send one month's supply. They didn't offer anything. Just a phone number if I wanted to call them back.

I called back, waited on hold several minutes, and left a voice message. With their track record, it could be days or weeks before I hear from them again, and meanwhile diabetes supplies have run out.< /Text>

<text>**FINAL UPDATE**
At first, I was very unhappy with ADS customer service for the reasons below. However, ADS was extremely proactive in remedying the situation and now I am extremely satisfied. As soon as my insurance approved the authorization, ADS got my order ready and out the door. I believe that my initial experience was not representative of ADS as a whole and I applaud their customer service department for going above and beyond to make sure I could get my supplies as fast as possible.

**UPDATE**
So, I'm actually really impressed with ADS customer service! Less than one day after I posted the original review, a rep contacted me and helped me get everything sorted out. It turns out we do need some more paperwork (which I found a little frustrating, because I was told multiple times by multiple reps that they had all the paperwork necessary and all I had to do was wait), but hopefully that was the last of the miscommunication. They also apologized for the lack of communication on behalf of the company and even offered to overnight me some testing materials so that I can check my blood sugars in the meantime. This interaction makes me hopeful that my previous experience with ADS was not representative of their customer service. I don't like leaving bad reviews on yelp, but I think that a company that deals with life-saving medical supplies should be held to a higher standard than say, a coffee shop. I will update this review hopefully just one more time after everything works out and I actually get my G6 system!

I've been trying to get on the Dexcom G6 and my experience with Advanced Diabetes Supply has extremely been frustrating. The process of getting the supplies I need has been delayed multiple times because different reps keep giving me the wrong information. They even sent a text message that an authorization had been submitted, but when I called to check in, it actually had not been submitted. To their credit, every rep I spoke to has been very friendly. My experience is detailed below:

ADS: "We spoke with your doctor's office yesterday, we have all the paperwork, and everything looks good. We'll give you a call when things are ready."

Me: *calls to check in two weeks later*

ADS: "Actually, we need your doctor's office to send us a form so we can send it to your insurance. After we get that, it'll take about a week for your insurance to approve it."

Me: ??? then why did you tell me everything was good and have me wait two weeks for nothing??? *Has doctor submit necessary paperwork in less than one day. calls ADS to check in a week later."

ADS: "Yes, we have all the paperwork and we just have to submit an authorization to your insurance. I'll submit it now, check back in a few days."

**They actually sent me a text message which states that the authorization was submitted as urgent and everything should be approved in about a week.

Me: *calls back a few days later to check AGAIN*

ADS: "Your authorization hasn't been submitted.... Yes, I see that someone sent you that text message, but they didn't actually submit the authorization. I'll submit it now and everything should be ready in about a week."

Me: ??????? Your company literally sent me a text message that my authorization had been submitted as "URGENT" and that I would only have to wait another week. Now my process of waiting a week is starting over??

Extremely frustrating... will be calling back tomorrow to see if they actually submitted the authorization.</text>< pictures>

< Text>
I usually only write positive reviews, but my experience with Advanced Diabetes Supply has been so frustrating that I just had to write a negative review.  First of all, getting someone on the phone is nearly impossible.  If you leave a message, it takes days for them to return your call.  I am a Type 1 diabetic that uses an insulin pump and must check my blood sugar 8 times a day.  Even with sending BG logs and office visit chart notes, I have never been able to be approved to get the number of test strips needed.  This last time, after talking with someone at ADS at least daily for 2 weeks and my doctor faxing the same information to them at least 4 times, I have transferred my prescription to WalMart.  If you use an insulin pump and are on Medicare Part B to cover your diabetes supplies, do not waste your time on Advanced Diabetes Supply!< /Text>

<time>1531694303610</time><rate>5<//rate><text>Highly recommend the beaf rib noodle(ÁâõËÇâÂπ≤ÊâØÈù¢). This noodle is the classic meal for farmers in the middle west part of china. That area is a plateau and always lack of water. At hot summer, farmers are pretty tired and thirsty when finishing a whole day's of work. So theirs wife will save the noodle in the cold water. When husband come back, they grap the noodle from water, add chili powder and vinegar on the top, then pour a touch of boiled oil to release the sour and spicy flavor. With this flavor, farmers could cheer up theirs spirit quickly and get cooled down from the hot weather. That's the history behind the dish. You could taste 90% genuinue flavor at this restaurant. RECOMMEND!</text><Pics>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipN1JByBwmF9YDjh-eGnpZ2FUHNv-1QjtWi0HbJj=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]< /Pics><Response>None<//Response><GmapID>0x80857c28b2404043:0x90056544a5c533c7<//GmapID></record>

< review>
Best. Bubble. Tea. In. LA. We used to bounce from place to place trying bubble tea until we found Refresh! Just so you know, this is the *freshest* tea you will taste! You can tell it's not powder and/or loaded with sugar. Though the passion fruit black tea is very good, my go-to is black milk tea with boba. There are other additional toppings you can add to your drink and you can also adjust the amount of ice (i.e. regular, less, etc.). If you're in the mood for baked good, try their amazing chocolate chip cookies! In addition to offering phenomenal products, Refresh is a small business and the owners are awesome. When you factor in all of the above, not sure what else you could ask for!< /review>

<text>Yes. The boba is delicious - soft and warm with just enough gumminess. One of the better shops for the boba. < text>
I love the staff at the shop which is really important for me since it's the closest one from my school. The boba is a really good amount of sweetness and chewiness and there's quite a lot compared to other shops I've been to for the regular amount (which is it you don't order the extra boba). The drinks themselves are also very good as well as the prices (unless you order add-ons, everything's mostly no more than $4.50). There aren't too many people (unless the occasional times where there's a long line) but they have really fast service and they almost always get my order right (but they always make it again if you ask). This is one of my top two favourite places :)< /text>

Was downtown and discovered this little gem on my trip to SD.  Their fish tacos are amazing! I just got the 2 fries tacos with waffle fries and boy did it bring joy to my taste buds. The 1/2 catfish plate special is a really great value. With a drink the whole thing was less than 10 bucks. (Without its a little over 7 with tax) Great for a quick lunch and they even have hotsauce to mix with ketchup for the criss cross fries served along side. They also provide a lemon which I like to mix into the tasty tartar sauce they serve. I couldn't help but take a bite before I took this picture because the smell was so yummy.< /Review>

<user_id>103040814040282726031< /user_id>< name>
Marlee Degele</name>
< time>
1546145203024</time>
<rating>5< /rating>< text>
My dad ordered the fried shrimp and ate every last bite, covered in chunky tarter without so much as a word. Waffle fries are crispy and very salty, and the cole slaw is best eaten flipped out of the dish so the juice (and flavor) no longer hides on the bottom. I ate every last chicken tender (4 tenders in the half order, w/ 4 bites of cole slaw, a side of ranch, and a heap of steaming waffle fries) but very sadly couldn't finish my fries. Worth the inexpensive price for hefty portions. Small parties acceptable in the restaurant, but our party of 5 +2 kids had a hard time squeezing in an almost full dining room.<//text>

<Text>Let me first say Google had the location wrong, it is at on C and 4th. I sent an update so hopefully they fix that.

I read the reviews and figured what the heck. When I got here at 1230 the place was packed. I ordered the fried fish burrito, fries, and Cole slaw $9.95 and a side of onion rings. The burrito was huge and for the money you can not go worng.

This appears to be a local joint. I didn't see any tourists walking in, which I view as a positive (I'm not from around here and like to eat where locals eat.) The place was clean and currently has an A rating posted.

Overall I gave it 3 stars because it wasn't the best burrito I had in my life. I was starving and the meal tasted good and filled me up. I had every intention of ordering more for a second round but couldn't fit it. I will definitely be back to try the grilled fish tacos.< /Text><Pictures>None< /Pictures>< Response>
None<//Response>

< date>

<Gmap_id>0x80d954a7c664ed1b:0xf3f20faffe87d9be< /Gmap_id>< text>
After reading the Yelp reviews I decided to give this place a try since I wanted shrimp but didn't want to spend a small fortune. I ordered a grilled shrimp taco and onion rings to go.  The food was cooked to order, I was in and out in 15 minutes.  For $4.50 the ship taco was large enough but not that flavorful, the onion rings were $3.25 and the portion size was enough to feed to people but again not that tasty.  The coating of the onion rings was cornmeal based which is different but I didn't particularly like it.  I doubt I will be back since that are a ton of seafood restaurants to explore down town.</text>

The other two packages were never found and Amazon had to reship them.

I was early for an eye exam in the shop next door, so I stopped in here yesterday for a sandwich.  I ordered an old fave, a grilled cheese, which arrived stuffed with cheese, and lightly toasted sourdough, not grilled and greasy. <text>Short story: Sandwiches are good but service is slowwwwwwww and not too friendly. If you are coming on your lunch time, choose another spot.

Long story: I moved to this area back in June of this year and I have been here 3x. 2 visits to dine in and 1 to go. Each time was slow. Doesn't matter the time of day.

The first visit which I was pretty excited because I love delis gave me a terrible impression. They forgot our order haha! I paid and I had the buzzer in my hand and was sitting at the table. I figured it was lunch time so I would be patient but no they forgot our order. I went up to them after about 15 mins and no one seemed to care that they forgot.
The second time they didn't forget our order but was still slow. The third time I figured place an order to go maybe.. just maybe it will be faster. No it wasn't.

I wanted to love this place but I'm afraid life is too short.<//text>< Pics>

Cool little park. Double tennis court, pretty sizable tree-covered table area, good-sized gazebo, playground, basketball court, and large field. Used to be homeless people coming through, mostly to use bathroom or sit down and rest and get away from sun, but didn't see any the last time I went.< /text>

< Review>
Not as crowded as the nearby lacy park, eaton blanche offers two playgrounds, smaller one for older kids and larger one for younger kids. The playgrounds are well maintained.

There is also a full court outdoor basketball court, tennis courts, multipurpose field, several picnic tables and bathrooms.<//Review>

<Rate>5< /Rate>< review>
Beautiful clean park. It's a medium sized park in my opinion but the jungle gym is large and there are two jungle gyms. My 15month old had a lot of fun. The basketball court finally has their hoops back up. The tennis courts are good and the baseball area is fine. You do need to bring your own plates for the baseball diamond though, which most people do. You also see a lot of people bringing soccer equipment for practices.< /review>

<Name>Jessica Salgado</Name><time>1557862557494</time><UserId.>114782672179142804233< /UserId.><resp>None<//resp>< Gmap_id>
0x80ec6c9c46e3abb9:0xa01b367b96190092<//Gmap_id>
<review>It's rare you walk into a place and think, wow I would love to work here. That's the friendly, fun and exciting atmosphere they give off! When you walk in you're greeted right away by beautiful, happy smiling faces. They walk you through checking in and you have a seat. The wait time is always short and they are always well staffed! All of this isn't even my favorite part...
What is so cool about this place are the incentives they give children to stay up on the things they are supposed to do.. they have an app called "the Hub" that the kids can accrue points on when they do certain things, like: a's on report card, cleanings at the dentist, coming to appointments, etc. my daughter has never been so excited to keep her teeth clean but now knowing those points turn into gift cards when she wants to turn them in... I've scene a difference. Such a great way to get kids on board with all of this (because she wasn't very excited).
Another awesome touch is the ice cream at the end. It isn't really about the ice cream per se to me but the excitement that they're getting a special treat and keeping these appointments upbeat and positive. My daughter feels like it's a special treat to walk into CCO and I hope this leads her to keep having a healthy and positive attitude when it comes to the dentist office.
I haven't even gotten to the actual medical stuff yet.. we have talk to other orthos that just kept telling me to wait.. wait.. wait. But the difference with Central Coast Ortho and the other offices are the depth of the initial consultation. Central Coast Ortho took pictures of my daughters profile, they took x rays and did a full exam. They were able to see some concerning issues that are not just cosmetic and could affect the future of her permanent front teeth. If I kept waiting and didn't get the consult from CCO I could very much be dealing with a much scarier issue when my daughter got older.
They presented me with all my options for her age.. they offer in house payment plans which make this journey a lot more feasible and they often have a monthly giveaway when you start up (my daughter got an iPad!- but this changes monthly)
If you're on the fence about what you should do with a child- or your own because they have adult patients too, I suggest going in and just talking to them. The first consult is free and you really have nothing to lose.</review><Rating>5< /Rating></record></dataset><record>

I came to see Dr. Specht for removal of an old permanent retainer and replacing it with a removable one. <user_id>116514291276227077938< /user_id><name>Linda Gadbois<//name>< date>
1494969761937</date>
<Rate>5< /Rate>< Text>
Thank you for telling us about your experience

Your Review:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
We met Dr. Specht after having consulted 2 other area orthodontists regarding my daughter's need for ortho treatment. I felt that the other orthos made a rush to judgment about removing 4 of my daughter's adult teeth immediately and then beginning treatment. Dr. Specht felt that we should wait until she'd lost all her baby teeth in order to determine if the removal of 4 adult teeth would indeed be necessary prior to applying braces. He saw her at regular intervals at no charge for almost 2 years before she lost all of her baby teeth. And guess what? It turned out that with just the baby teeth gone... there was enough room in her mouth to accommodate ALL of her adult teeth. Voila! Good call Dr. Specht! Your patience and good judgment paid off on Delilah's behalf!! We love the care and service we've received from you and your staff from beginning to end. Delilah will soon be getting her braces off and her teeth look BEAUTIFUL!!!<//Text>

<user>116909191096483400223</user>< review>
I have two sons currently in Invisalign at Central Coast Orthodontics with Dr. Specht. I was absolutely blown away by their kindness at our consult appointment. The front office is so happy to see you when you walk in.  I'm not kidding when I say that every single person that we have come in contact with at their office, has treated us with warmth and greets us with a smile on the their face. My kids love it here as well. The environment is welcoming and fun. They are always having contests and prizes and have fun things going on at the office. We got treated to a full Taco bar on Cinco De Mayo. Of course my kids would say that their favorite part was getting free iPads when they started their Invisalign. (That was the promotion going on at that time but they always change it up.) They also get to choose an ice cream from the ice cream bar at every visit when they leave. Most important to me is the the doctors are knowledgeable and really help you to understand all your options and make you feel so comfortable as well as the kids. I highly recommend this office to anyone looking to improve their smile. You will not be disappointed coming here!!!< /review>
